node.title: Three Auckland nightclubs listed as Covid-19 locations of interest
node.description: Three central Auckland nightclubs have been listed as Covid-19 'close contact' locations of interest.
node.content:
["Three central Auckland nightclubs have been listed as Covid-19 'close contact' locations of interest.", "", "
Longroom Bar and Nightclub in Grey Lynn was named as a location of interest on 19 January. Photo: Google Maps
", "The Ministry of Health listed the affected locations and times as follows:", "The ministry advises people who there at those times to self-isolate, test immediately and test again on day five after exposure at the location of interest.", "Further isolation and testing requirements will be provided your results emerge. You should also record your visit online or call Healthline so contact tracers can get in touch.", "Meanwhile, the Ara-Tai Cafe in the suburb of Half Moon Bay has also been listed as a close contact location of interest for customers seated inside on 18 January, between 12.30pm and 2pm.", "The same advice as above applies if you were seated inside, the ministry said."]
